-- U.S. Corn Planting in 2011 Will Climb to Four-Year High, Informa Predicts
-- B y   J e f f   W i l s o n
-- 2010-11-11T16:36:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/u-s-corn-planting-in-2011-will-climb-to-four-year-high-informa-predicts.html
U.S. corn planting will rise to
93.055 million acres next year, compared with 88.222 million
that the government estimated was sown in 2010, Memphis,
Tennessee-based researcher Informa Economics Inc. said today in
a report to clients. Planting next year will be the highest
since 2007, Informa said. In September, Informa forecast farmers
would plant 90.39 million next year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Wilson in Chicago at 
 jwilson29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
